Content:: This article documents the chronology and epidemiology of SARS-CoV-2, the virus that causes the coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19) and is responsible for the COVID-19 pandemic, in February 2021. The first human cases of COVID-19 were identified in Wuhan, China, in December 2019. World Health Organization weekly report:[7] World Health Organization weekly report:[45] World Health Organization weekly report:[85] World Health Organization weekly report:[122] World Health Organization weekly report:[136] No new countries or territories confirmed their first cases during February 2021. By the end of February, only the following countries and territories have not reported any cases of SARS-CoV-2 infections, although some claims are disputed or challenged: Africa Asia Europe Oceania
